<TITLE> RAB raids home of Purbani director, widens search for 'girlfriend' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, October 29 (bdnews24.com)  The Rapid Action Battalion seized up to 400 bottles of alcoholic beverages in an overnight raid on the home of a Purbani Hotel director in Dhanmondi early Tuesday as the elite force widened its search for his girlfriend with links to Yaba tablets. Several RAB officers told bdnews24.com that they had launched the raid on the building on Road No. 27 of Dhanmondi in search of Jannatul Ferdous, a model. The woman, 22 years of age according to details in her passport seized by the RAB, was described as girlfriend of Mahbubur Rahman Joynal, director of the hotel. "We are surprised to find the huge quantity of foreign liquor here. We are in search of Jannatul Ferdous," wing commander Sultan Mohammad Khan Nurani, who led the raid, told bdnews24.com correspondent Abu Noman Sajib on the scene. The commanding officer for RAB-3 said the RAB team would continue the search. Major Imrul Kayes Chowdhury, a member of the RAB team, said they have information that a huge quantity of Yaba was stashed away in the building. Jannatul, nicknamed Nikki, had long been living in the building, said another RAB officer, Khalid Shams. After two hours of the raid, the RAB officers took a break. bdn
